## A Closure Managing a Round-Robin Pool

A closure that cycles through a list of items (e.g., API keys, endpoints) in round-robin fashion, useful for load balancing or rate limiting.

```scheme
;; A round-robin selector for a pool of items.
(define make-round-robin
  (lambda (items)
    (let ((pool items)
          (index 0))
      (lambda ()
        (if (null? pool)
            'empty-pool
            (let ((item (list-ref pool index)))
              (set! index (modulo (+ index 1) (length pool)))
              item))))))

(define rr (make-round-robin '(key-a key-b key-c)))

(list
  (rr)   ;; => key-a
  (rr)   ;; => key-b
  (rr)   ;; => key-c
  (rr)   ;; => key-a
  (rr))  ;; => key-b
```

The closure captures `pool` and `index`. Each call returns the item at `index` and increments `index`, wrapping around with `modulo`. This is BACK: the simplest round-robin that works, no extra bookkeeping.

