## A Closure with Conditional State Reset

A closure that accumulates values but resets its state if a special \"reset\" signal is passed.

```scheme
;; An accumulator that resets on a special signal.
(define make-resettable-accumulator
  (lambda (reset-signal)
    (let ((total 0))
      (lambda (value)
        (if (equal? value reset-signal)
            (begin
              (set! total 0)
              'reset)
            (begin
              (set! total (+ total value))
              total))))))

(define acc (make-resettable-accumulator 'reset))

(list
  (acc 5)       ;; => 5
  (acc 10)      ;; => 15
  (acc 'reset)  ;; => reset
  (acc 3))      ;; => 3
```

The closure captures `total`. Each call checks if the value is the reset signal. If so, reset `total` to zero and return `'reset`. Otherwise, add the value to `total` and return the new sum. This is ESCAPE in code: the reset signal is a controlled failure path that cleanly resets state.

