  (wc-pipeline \"https://example.com\")   ;; => (words <n> total-fetched 1)
  (wc-pipeline \"https://example.org\"))  ;; => (words <n> total-fetched 2)
```

The closure captures `history`. Each call fetches the URL. If fetch fails, return `'fetch-failed`. Otherwise, extract text and count words. If count fails, return `'count-failed`. Otherwise, log the URL and count, and return the count plus the total number of fetches. This is FORWARD in a three-stage pipeline, with ESCAPE at each verb call.

