  (multi-model \"What is 2+2?\"))   ;; => (prompt \"What is 2+2?\" count 3 responses (<r1> <r2> <r3>))
```

The closure captures `history`. Each call invokes all three model verbs. It filters out any that failed, then builds a summary of the successful responses. If all failed, return `'all-models-failed`. Otherwise, log the summary and return it. This is FORWARD in a fan-out pattern: we call multiple verbs in parallel (conceptually) and aggregate the results, with ESCAPE for failures.

