  (splitter '(5 6 7 8))     ;; => (true (2 4 6 8) false (1 3 5 7))
  (splitter '(9 10)))       ;; => (true (2 4 6 8 10) false (1 3 5 7 9))
```

The closure captures `true-bucket` and `false-bucket`. Each call walks the input values, applying the predicate and routing each value to the appropriate bucket. It returns both buckets. This is FORWARD: we route values conditionally, building up two independent states.

