## A Closure Managing a Queue with Size Limit

A closure that maintains a FIFO queue with a maximum size: when full, enqueueing drops the oldest item.

```scheme
;; A bounded FIFO queue.
(define make-bounded-queue
  (lambda (max-size)
    (let ((queue '()))
      (lambda (op . args)
        (cond
          ((eq? op 'enqueue)
           (let ((item (car args)))
             (set! queue (append queue (list item)))
             (if (> (length queue) max-size)
                 (set! queue (cdr queue))
                 'ok)
             (length queue)))
          ((eq? op 'dequeue)
           (if (null? queue)
               'empty
               (let ((item (car queue)))
                 (set! queue (cdr queue))
                 item)))
          ((eq? op 'size)
           (length queue))
          (else 'unknown-op))))))

(define q (make-bounded-queue 3))

(list
  (q 'enqueue 'a)    ;; => 1
  (q 'enqueue 'b)    ;; => 2
  (q 'enqueue 'c)    ;; => 3
  (q 'enqueue 'd)    ;; => 3 (drops 'a)
  (q 'dequeue)       ;; => b
  (q 'size))         ;; => 2
```

The closure captures `queue`. On `'enqueue`, append the item and trim the queue if it exceeds `max-size`. On `'dequeue`, return and remove the first item. On `'size`, return the length. This is BACK: the simplest bounded queue that works, no complex data structure needed.

