## A Closure with Recursive Data Collection

A closure that walks a nested list structure, collecting all leaf values into a flat list, and remembers all leaves seen across multiple calls.

```scheme
;; A leaf collector that flattens nested lists and accumulates across calls.
(define make-leaf-collector
  (lambda ()
    (let ((all-leaves '()))
      (lambda (tree)
        (define (collect t)
          (cond
            ((null? t) '())
            ((pair? t) (append (collect (car t)) (collect (cdr t))))
            (else (list t))))
        (let ((new-leaves (collect tree)))
          (set! all-leaves (append all-leaves new-leaves))
          (list 'new new-leaves 'total all-leaves))))))

(define collector (make-leaf-collector))

(list
  (collector '(1 (2 3) 4))       ;; => (new (1 2 3 4) total (1 2 3 4))
  (collector '((5) 6))           ;; => (new (5 6) total (1 2 3 4 5 6))
  (collector '(7 (8 (9)))))      ;; => (new (7 8 9) total (1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 9))
```

The closure captures `all-leaves`. Each call recursively flattens the input tree, appends the new leaves to `all-leaves`, and returns both the new leaves and the full accumulated list. This is FORWARD: we advance the state recursively, building up a flat collection over time.

